Process called "aes_fill_inv_sbox" takes inv_sbox as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Initializes the 256-byte inverse S-box per FIPS 197 figure 14.
    Used during AES decryption. The inverse S-box satisfies
    InvSBox[SBox[x]] = x for all x in [0, 255].
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Writes the 256 hardcoded byte values from FIPS 197 figure 14 in
    row-major order.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    256 byte stores. One-shot table initialization per decrypt op.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Public table.
    @End Security_Scope

